INSERT INTO `blog_comments` (`id`, `post_id`, `comment_by`, `comment_email`, `comment_date`, `comment`, `status`) VALUES
(1, 3, 'Jeffrey Black', 'noreply@blogger.com', '2014-05-16', 'Good point, Tim. Every part of the customer experience counts. <br /><br />Interestingly, I read this tip about using a can opener for those nasty plastic clamshells http://www.wikihow.com/Open-Rigid-Plastic-Clamshell-Packages-Safely. It works great and keeps you safe from the sharp plastic edges.<br /><br />I enjoy reading your blog. ~ Jeff', 1),
(2, 6, 'Genevieve Flight', 'noreply@blogger.com', '2014-05-07', 'You rock Tim. People like you with positive mind are very rare to find. Hopefully connect with you on LinkedIn soon. Million thanks for your inspiration..', 1),
(3, 8, 'Gem King', 'noreply@blogger.com', '2014-05-06', 'Principle takes us to success and pride takes us to failure.Well said, Tim!', 1),
(4, 9, 'GSPIZZO DATATACTS &amp; ICT CENTRE', 'noreply@blogger.com', '2014-05-05', 'Thank You. Well noted', 1),
(5, 18, 'Shelley Wilson', 'noreply@blogger.com', '2014-04-25', 'Lovely post! I&#39;ve just started yet another health regime so can relate.  Couple of great books I&#39;ve read recently that may help - Cut the Crap, Loss Weight Fast by Richard Shaw and How to Eat  Everything and Stay Slim by Peter Jones and Della Galton, they are refreshingly funny and full of simple ideas. Good luck and thanks for sharing :-)', 1),
(6, 23, 'blake mendez', 'noreply@blogger.com', '2014-05-18', 'hello tim.  where has this idea applied in your own life with your professional and/or personal efforts?', 1),
(7, 24, 'Steven Webb', 'noreply@blogger.com', '2014-04-05', 'Exactly, enthusiasm and excitement is brilliant for one-offs. But do very little for changing habits.', 1),
(8, 26, 'Unknown', 'noreply@blogger.com', '2014-04-28', 'Just what we all need to remember -and some need to learn. <br />', 1),
(9, 26, 'Tanal Azam', 'noreply@blogger.com', '2014-04-15', 'It&#39;s that the human nature, mistake is an act which lead you to jump another time to the sky if you truly repent, what we need is to be always in the side of right, do our best to do it.', 1),
(10, 28, 'chibuikeblog', 'noreply@blogger.com', '2014-05-02', 'These simple words are very deep and insightful. Thanks Tim. Its time to get terrible for greatness.', 1),
(11, 32, 'Roxann Souci', 'noreply@blogger.com', '2014-03-24', 'Just found your book on Amazon! It&#39;s like an MBA, a revival meeting, and a great margarita all rolled up into one. ', 1),
(12, 32, 'Knucklepop Brand', 'noreply@blogger.com', '2014-03-15', 'Hello Tim,  I would like to do a celebrity interview with you to post on my blog. Let me know, have an exceptional day! Peace...', 1),
(13, 32, 'Aneesha Mourya', 'noreply@blogger.com', '2014-03-14', 'A perfect strategy it is to get millions of people reading you! Thank you Tim for this valuable piece of advice. #Twog', 1),
(14, 34, 'Bill', 'noreply@blogger.com', '2014-04-26', 'A simple yet elegant post.  Say what?', 1),
(15, 34, 'Alison Andersen', 'noreply@blogger.com', '2014-03-18', 'Hi Tim, I&#39;m new to your blog having been led here by the above article, which is excellent!  I couldn&#39;t agree more about the need for (and sadly-lacking frequency of!) listening.  Clear verbal communication is absolutely vital to our existence, not only in business but in our day to day lives. So many problems arise from 2 parties not explaining clearly what they want/need/expect and your lawn-mowing story is a great example!! ', 1),
(16, 40, 'rams legna', 'noreply@blogger.com', '2014-01-11', 'get set go...........................!!!<br />', 1),
(17, 41, 'The Observer', 'noreply@blogger.com', '2013-12-28', 'I concur that it is disrespectful not to show appreciation! TY 4 Acknowledging. â˜†', 1),
(18, 41, 'The Observer', 'noreply@blogger.com', '2013-12-28', 'Hello, I concur with the fact that it&#39;s disrespectful not to show appreciation! TY 4 Acknowledging. ', 1),
(19, 42, 'Kathy', 'noreply@blogger.com', '2013-12-12', 'We need more people like you on twitter. Scratch that.  We need more people like you everywhere....', 1),
(20, 48, 'Jayne Saul-Paterson', 'noreply@blogger.com', '2014-04-19', 'Interesting..  so we know that only a few people can win that gold medal for swimming and this suggests that the right foundation i.e. diet, training, motivation etc is pretty well-matched with others who compete but don&#39;t win medals etc and the key difference is technique however what about mental strategies ie single minded focus, overcoming limiting beliefs - isn&#39;t training the mind to succeed the ultimate technique ? ', 1),
(21, 51, 'Amy Loynes', 'noreply@blogger.com', '2014-04-16', 'The trouble with lying and deceiving is that their efficiency depends entirely upon a clear notion of the truth that the liar and deceiver wishes to hide.~~Hannah Arendt', 1),
(22, 56, 'Kate', 'noreply@blogger.com', '2013-08-29', 'I would have entered had I known about it! I don&#39;t mind writing, actually I quite enjoy it, &amp;.I know I could have used the money. Oh well, maybe next time. Keep posting great quotes &amp; insured Tim, I enjoy the reads &amp; learn something with each one posted. ', 1),
(23, 61, 'Jessica Stead', 'noreply@blogger.com', '2014-05-14', 'I liked this post a lot, especially &quot;Occasionally someone gets remarkably lucky, but more often, failure is the road you will be driving on far longer than you want, if you hope to succeed.&quot; It was the reminder I needed this week. Thankfully the world is full of wonderful people like your parents. Thanks for sharing Tim.  ', 1);

